<subSubSection pageId="12" pageNumber="13" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1437,151,536]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,319,367,392]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Males of this species are defferentiated from 
<taxonomicName box="[885,1114,369,392]" class="Insecta" family="Gerridae" genus="Rheumatobates" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="minutus" subSpecies="minutus">
<emphasis box="[885,1114,369,392]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">R. minutus minutus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
because the fore femur is expanded at basal 
<number box="[357,372,404,428]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="2.0">2</number>
/ 
<number box="[382,395,404,428]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="3.0">3</number>
, with a row of ten spines along lateroventral margin, which is doubled at basal half. Females have the anterior margin of metasternum concave; the connexiva is short and subquadrate at apex, with short setae; the tergite VIII is subrectangular, longer than wide; the gonocoxae are slightly directed upward.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
